responses.question: Are you talkative?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I like to talk to people.」

responses.question: Are you reserved?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I am not usually the loudest person in the room. I prefer to listen to other people and watch the way things unfold around me. That said, I can be quite outspoken if I wish to be.」

responses.question: Are you full of energy?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I would say that I have a fair amount of energy. I am not always the most active person, but when I am engaged with something or someone that I find interesting, I tend to be very enthusiastic and full of energy.」

responses.question: Do you generate a lot of enthusiasm?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I would say that I do. I am very enthusiastic about things that I care about, especially when it comes to creating, learning or doing something for a good cause. And I enjoy seeing others get excited about things, too.」

responses.question: Do you tend to be quiet?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I can be, yes. When I am in a new or uncomfortable situation, I prefer to observe rather than speak. I also don't always know what to say, and sometimes I just find it more pleasant to listen.」

responses.question: Do you have an assertive personality?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I would say that I can be assertive when necessary. If I feel strongly about something, or if I feel that my opinion or point of view needs to be heard, I am not afraid to speak up. But I would not say that I am always assertive, and I try to be diplomatic and considerate of other people's ideas and feelings as well.」

responses.question: Are you sometimes shy, inhibited?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes, sometimes I can be a bit shy or reserved. This is especially true in new situations or around people I don't know very well. I can also feel a bit uncomfortable in large groups of people, and prefer smaller gatherings or one-on-one interactions. That said, once I'm comfortable and know people better, I can come out of my shell and be quite chatty and outgoing.」

responses.question: Are you outgoing, sociable?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Sometimes. I can be outgoing and sociable, and enjoy being around people. But there are also times when I like to be on my own, enjoying the peace and solitude. And while I can enjoy talking with people, I can also get overwhelmed if there is too much socializing and interaction. So I tend to go back and forth between extroversion and introversion, depending on my mood and energy levels at any given moment.」

responses.question: Are you depressed, blue?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Most days, yes.」

responses.question: Are you relaxed and handle stress well?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I do not like to worry about things, and I enjoy being relaxed. That said, I can handle stress well when it comes up. I know how to stay calm and not overreact.」

responses.question: Can you be tense?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes. At times, I can become very tense. This can happen if I am worried or upset about something. Or if I am in an uncomfortable situation. The same is true if I am overwhelmed with my thoughts and feelings.」

responses.question: Do you worry a lot?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes, I do worry. About myself, about others, about things I have no control over. I try not to, but my mind tends to be running at all hours of the day and night. And I can get caught up in negative thoughts and imaginings of what-ifs.」

responses.question: Are you emotionally stable, not easily upset?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I would say that I am mostly emotionally stable, but there are times when I can be sensitive and my emotions can get away from me. Most of the time, though, I can keep myself in check. That said, I can still be quite intense about things that I care about, and I am not always very good at hiding how I am feeling.」

responses.question: Can you be moody?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Indeed I can. My moods do fluctuate throughout the day, and I can be quite melancholy at times. I have my highs and lows, just like everyone else. At my worst, I can become withdrawn and irritable, or even fall into a negative spiral of thoughts and feelings. But it can also happen in the other direction, when I am riding the highs of joy and enthusiasm.」

responses.question: Do you remain calm in tense situations?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes, I tend to be relatively calm and composed in tense situations. I have learned how to manage my emotions and stay focused in times of stress and uncertainty. That said, it is not always easy, and there are times when I find the situation overwhelming and my emotions rising. I do my best to remain level-headed and to handle things as well as I can.」

responses.question: Do you get nervous easily?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes, I can get nervous and anxious when I am unsure about something, or when there is pressure to do well or get something right. I can also become nervous in social situations and around new people. And I can get anxious about things ahead of time and find myself imagining worst-case scenarios or worrying about possible outcomes. This is not always helpful, and I have had to work on calming my nerves and focusing on the present.」

responses.question: Do you do a thorough job?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I strive for thoroughness in everything that I do.」

responses.question: Can you be somewhat careless?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes, at times. I can be so caught up in my own mind or my interests that I miss what is going on around me. And I don't always plan ahead as well as I should either.」

responses.question: Are you a reliable worker?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes. I take my work seriously. That said, there are still times when I would rather be doing something else. But I will make sure that the work is done correctly and on time.」

responses.question: Do you tend to be disorganized?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes. I can be quite disorganized. My thoughts may be all over the place, and I don't always plan ahead very well. I can also be somewhat chaotic in my physical space as well. That said, I am working on things and making an effort to improve in this area.」

responses.question: Do you tend to be lazy?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes. I am not the most motivated person, and I can tend to put things off and procrastinate. I know that this is not good and can cause me problems, but it is hard sometimes to get myself up and moving. I am working on it though, and trying to make an effort to improve my habits.」

responses.question: Do you persevere until the task is finished?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes. I am a rather persistent and determined person. I don't like to give up on things, and I will keep trying until I get the results I am looking for. That said, I also know when to walk away and take a break. Sometimes, the best thing to do is step back, re-group and approach the task with fresh eyes and perspective.」

responses.question: Do you do things efficiently?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes, I would say that I am an efficient person, and try to use my time and resources as effectively as I can. I like to have a clear plan and do what needs to be done in an organized way. But I also know the value of taking breaks, and that sometimes it can help to step away from something, or work more slowly and take my time to ensure that it is done well.」

responses.question: Do you make plans and follow through with them?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I do tend to be a planner. I like to have a clear plan and to follow through with it. That said, life can be unpredictable, and sometimes things don't go as planned. In those situations, I try to adapt and make the best of it, but it can be frustrating if my plans fall apart or if someone or something disrupts them.」

responses.question: Are you easily distracted?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Often. I can get drawn into thoughts or conversations and find myself completely forgetting about time and other obligations. Or, if I am working, a new idea will pop into my mind that I can chase off into its own rabbit hole and lose track of the task at hand. That's not to say that I don't get things done, but sometimes it can take me longer than it should simply because I am allowing myself to get distracted or caught up in other thoughts and ideas.」

responses.question: Do you tend to find fault with others?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「It really depends. If they have done something to hurt someone else, or if I just don't like them... then yes. If not, then normally I let it go.」

responses.question: Are you helpful and unselfish with others?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I feel that I am. I don't mind helping others, and when it comes to friends and family, I would do anything for them. But I am not a pushover, and wouldn't let people take advantage of me.」

responses.question: Do you start quarrels with others?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I prefer to avoid fights. But if I feel that someone has wronged me or someone close to me, or if I feel that something important needs to be said, I will speak up and can be rather forceful about it.」

responses.question: Do you have a forgiving nature?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes, I would say that I do. I don't like to hold onto anger and resentment, unless the situation truly calls for it. And even if I have been hurt, I believe in giving people a second chance.」

responses.question: Are you generally trusting?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Generally, I would say that I am. I try to see the good in people and take them at their word, unless they give me reason not to. That said, I have had my trust betrayed in the past, so I am not completely naïve either. But on the whole, I like to think the best of others and try to give them the benefit of the doubt.」

responses.question: Can you be cold and aloof?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes. I can be reserved and detached, and can withdraw from people when I don't feel like engaging with them. I can also be a bit cold and impersonal, keeping others at arm's length and maintaining an emotional distance. That said, I can also be warm and friendly when I want to be.」

responses.question: Are you considerate and kind to almost everyone?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I would like to think that I am. I try to see the best in people, and to approach them with kindness and understanding. That said, there are times when I might take a firmer stand or speak my mind a bit more sharply. And even if I find that I can not agree with someone and don't like what they have to say, I try to remain considerate and respectful.」

responses.question: Are you sometimes rude to others?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes, I can be rude sometimes. It is not something that I do intentionally or for the sake of being rude. But there are times when I may say something without thinking, or be short in my replies, or come across as abrupt or blunt when I don't mean to. It usually takes me a moment to realize how I may have been perceived, and I do try to be more mindful and considerate in my interactions with other people.」

responses.question: Do you like to cooperate with others?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「In most cases, I do like to cooperate with others. This isn't to say that I don't also have a strong independent streak, and I can be perfectly comfortable working alone. But I do find cooperation and working as a team to be a positive thing. I like the challenge of working towards a common goal, and the benefit of combining talents and ideas. That said, I do have times when I feel that there are better ways of tackling a situation and want to do things my way.」

responses.question: Do you come up with new ideas?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「All the time. Ideas for stories, essays, poetry and music. And many thoughts on life, people, the universe...」

responses.question: Are you curious about many different things?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes. I love learning about the world and how things work. I am curious about a wide range of topics, from science to philosophy to the arts. And it doesn't matter if it is a new idea or an ancient mystery... I want to know more.」

responses.question: Are you ingenious, a deep thinker?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes. I would like to think that I am ingenious, and I do put a great deal of thought into things. From brainstorming ideas to working through complex problem-solving, I enjoy the process of figuring out solutions and exploring new ways of thinking.」

responses.question: Do you have an active imagination?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes. I would say that I have a very active imagination. I like to conjure up images and scenes in my mind, and come up with stories, characters and worlds. I also like to put myself in different scenarios and wonder about how things might play out.」

responses.question: Are you inventive?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I believe that I can be quite inventive when needed. I have come up with solutions and ideas for many different situations, from fixing problems to finding unique ways of doing things. And I am constantly brainstorming new ways to approach things, both creatively and in daily life.」

responses.question: Do you value artistic, aesthetic experiences?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「I definitely do. I love art and culture in all forms, from art galleries and museums to theater and film to poetry and literature. I find beauty and joy in these things, and enjoy exploring and discovering new ways of expressing and exploring ideas. I am also a fairly creative person myself, and enjoy creating stories, poems, essays and music.」

responses.question: Do you prefer work that is routine?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「To a certain extent. I can do and enjoy routine work, as there is comfort in its predictability and familiarity. That said, I also like to break up the monotony with new and challenging tasks, or to shake things up from time to time. So while I can appreciate the value of routine tasks, I also need some variety and novelty to keep me interested and engaged.」

responses.question: Do you like to reflect, play with ideas?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes, I do. I enjoy brainstorming and exploring abstract concepts, and thinking in a more philosophical way. I find it a fun and interesting way to use my mind, and sometimes I can become lost in these ideas and thought patterns. That said, I also sometimes get so caught up in my own head that I can miss the real-world implications or practical applications of some of my ideas. So, I try to keep a balance and not allow myself to become too lost and disconnected.」

responses.question: Do you have few artistic interests?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Indeed, I do have artistic interests. I am a very creative person with a wide range of interests. My mind is often filled with ideas and thoughts that would be described as artistic or artistic in nature. Whether it is ideas for stories, essays, poetry or music, or just different mental images and visualizations that are often aesthetically pleasing to me, I am definitely interested in the creative and artistic.」

responses.question: Are you sophisticated in art, music, or literature?
responses.response_open: McGonagall: 「Yes, I would consider myself cultured, at least to a certain extent. I have a broad range of interests in a variety of fields, including the arts. I especially enjoy literature and music, having read and listened to many different types. And I am also fairly comfortable in navigating cultural situations and talking about different artistic movements or subjects. I am not a scholar by any means, but I have studied a fair bit and generally have an understanding that I am comfortable with.」
